{{see|Nix}}
==English==

===Etymology===
Dutch : "niks".(nothing) Although it's slang for "niets" (nothing), it is in the Dutch dictionary and is used by virtually all classes of society.
 
Maybe also from German: "nichts", pronounced [nɪçtz], colloquial "nix" [nɪkz], meaning "nothing"

===Noun===
{{en-noun-unc}}

# {{colloquial}}: [[nothing]].

====Synonyms====
*[[nada]]
*[[zip]]

====Translations====
*Afrikaans: [[niks]]
*Spanish: [[nada]]
*French: que dalle

===Verb===
{{en-verb|nix|es}}

# To make something become nothing; to [[reject]].
#:'''''Nix''' the last order - the customer walked out.''

===Related terms===
*[[86]] / [[eighty-six]]
*[[ixnay]]

